content.title: Alarplasty Thailand- Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Among all the features that a person has on their face the nose is the important. When the nose has a beautiful shape, provides balance to the face, the beauty of the face is enhanced. So if you have a nose that’s you feel is in a little help then alarplasty Thailandis ideal for you.

Alarplasty is the process of narrowing the span of the nostrils as well as the alar base. The surgical technique that’s used depends on the shape of your nostrils and the proportion of the nose to your whole face. The majority of the time alarplasty is done at the same time as the rhinoplasty if the alar if the patient have a nose that is too wide. Having this procedure done in combination with alarplasty Thailandwill result in a better appearance so the surgeon will make the decision about whether the procedure needs to be done or not.

Before you have the surgery, of course, you have to inform the surgeon about the allergies that you suffer from, any medical condition that you have as well as the medications you’re being prescribed and make sure to mention any non-prescription drugs you’re taking. There are also some things that you should avoid, such as Heparin, Coumadin and aspirin and any other medicines that contain aspirin before the week of your surgery, in order, to decrease the chance of bleeding.

After the first, night of the surgery, usually patients feel discomfort in the nose area, however, the pain can be decreased with a combination of medication that the patient receives after the procedure. Patients also sleep with their head higher that the chest as to reduce the swelling of the nose to make the alarplasty Thailandrecovery as quick as possible.

The second and third day after the procedure, you won’t feel any pain, but there will be a sufficient amount of swelling in the nose and eyelid area. The majority of patients have only experience swelling, but no bruising. There are only a few cases in which patients have experienced in the dorsum in the nose.

After, one week of the surgery 80% of the swelling will decrease. The other 20% of the swelling will take longer to heal. It takes about three weeks to get back to your normal appearance. You’ll be able to wash your face and shower as normal the second day after the surgery, however, you won’t be able to do any activity or be in any position that will increase pressure to the face, which will cause the swelling to prolong. Seven days after, the surgery you’ll go back to the clinic and the stitches will be removed.

When everything is said and done, after the alarplasty Thailandyou can expect that the result of the operation is guaranteed for a year. In most cases, if there’s a need for correction there will be no charge. So when you get this surgery done you’ll have the nose that you always wanted and complete the look of beauty.

content.title: Cheek Reduction Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Some people are happy with the look of their cheeks, however, there are others that hate the sight of it and are conscious about the, buccal fat. They often complain about how chubby and round their cheeks are, but there’s a solution that’ll fix the fat at give them back their confidence. They can opt for cheek reduction Thailand.

The buccal fat, that so many hate are the pads of fat are in the lower area of the cheeks. These “chipmunk cheeks” are from many different causes, such as being overweight and a genetic predisposition can also be another cause. Cheek reduction Thailand, also known as buccal fat removal, is a great solution if you want to decrease their cheeks size. The removal of the fat pads may contour the face and slim down the cheeks. This will help you to create the more hollowed and chiseled appearance.

The procedure of removing fat from the cheeks is straight forward, which is preformed by make an cut on the inside of the mouth. IV sedation or local anesthesia can be used and the procedure can last for about an hour. During the recovery time you’ll feel little pain, but the face will seem to be more swollen for about two weeks. It’ll take about 6-8 weeks until you see the final effects of the surgery.

However, before you decide to have cheek reduction Thailandyou need to think about the fact that as you age facial fat will decrease. If your mom and dad have faces that are slender, what you may have is considered “baby fat”. So if you have this procedure done at a young age, and you have the tendency to slender as you age then you might have a gaunt and drawn appearance by the time you reach your early thirties. So think about this getting this procedure closely.

If you want to make sure that you have a successful outcome of the surgery is the selection that you make. There are some people that will gain more advantages from having cheek augmentation including cheek implants. In other, circumstances a person may get more benefit from both, buccal fat removal and cheek implants. You and your surgeon will decide whether you should have reduction, implants or both.

Since cosmetic surgery is so popular, in addition, to cheek reductions, it’s advantageous to do your research and be able to come to an understanding the issues that are involved in the procedure. Such as what the surgery will and will not be able to accomplish, the risk, prices and other important factors involved with cheek reduction Thailand.

If you decide that cheek reduction Thailandis the right choice for you then you’ll no doubt get the results that you want as long as you have realistic expectations of what the surgery can do for you. Once you do understand everything that’s involved with the cheek reduction procedure then you will have slender cheeks that everyone will be envious of.

content.title: Chin Augmentation Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Have you ever thought about changing or enhancing the appearance of you chin? If you have that means that most likely you’re not happy with the way your chin looks. Well, that’s okay, there’s a simple solution that will give you the chin that will enhance your facial features and give you that boost in self-esteem that you need. All you have to do is consider chin augmentation Thailand, however, before, you begin your quest there are some things that you should know, starting with what chin augmentation is.

Chin augmentation is a procedure in which the whole goal is to reshape or enhance the size of the chin through the method of reshaping the existing bone or by the placement of a prosthetic chin implant. If this sounds like something that you wish to do then chin augmentation Thailandmight be the prefect option for you. The next, thing that you should be concerned with is how the procedure is done.

Chin surgery can take between 30 minutes to an hour to complete. The chin procedure can be preformed either under local anesthesia or general anesthesia, in addition, to sedation. The majority of procedures involve an incision being made inside the mouth on the lower lip or on the skin underneath the chin. The surgeon then will insert the implant through the incision and moves it into place, and then he closes the incision with sutures. For about one week after the surgery, the surgeon may tape the skin with pressure dressing.

There are some reasons why people decide to do chin augmentation Thailand. Some seek chin augmentation to increase or decrease the size of the chin by changing the structure underlying the chin providing a better balance to your facial features. Some may even choose to this procedure to correct an injury or a birth defect. In addition, to this information you also need to be aware of the risk involved.

You never know the what the results of an augmentation will be, however, the complications are rare and are minor. Although, this is the case there are some risk that you should be aware of. The risk can include:

Blood clotsInfectionDisplacement or movement of the implantSwelling and bruisingReaction to the anestheticsThe swelling and the bruising that you’ll experience should last for at least two weeks, but in sometimes the evidence of the swelling and bruising can last for up to two months. However, you can decrease these risk by following what your surgeon tells you. To do after the chin augmentation Thailand.

You’re a good candidate for the augmentation surgery if you have a weak chin, but have a dental bite that is normal. Whatever, the case may be, though, the surgeon will make the final decision as to whether or not you’ll be eligible after you have had an examination and a consolation for the chin augmentation Thailand.
Once you meet all the requirements you’ll be able to have the surgery and have the chin that you desire.

content.title: Chin Shaving Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: A person’s chin has to be just right and if it’s too long then it can throw off the look that you’re trying to achieve. You can have the size chin that you desire by simply making arrangements for chin shaving Thailand. In less than an hour, thirty minutes, you can have the chin that you always wished you had.

Once you have decided to have chin shaving Thailand, the surgery is preformed by making incisions in the mouth or underneath the chin. You surgeon, will then sculpt you chin to a shape that’s more pleasing in size. For the orthognathic surgery there will be an incision made inside the mouth and the facial bones will be repositioned. Depending on the extent of the work, the procedure can take up to an hour to three hours to complete.

Before you have the surgery preformed there are some things that you need to make sure that you inform your surgeon about, such as any allergies to environmental elements, foods and drugs that you may have. You should also avoid taking aspirin or any medications that contain aspirin two weeks before you have the procedure.

Once the chin shaving Thailandhas been completed, generally, the surgeon will apply dressings that’ll remain on the chin for two or three days, and you’ll experience a little tenderness. Any discomfort that you may feel can be kept under control with pain medication. Since chewing will be limited after the surgery, you’ll be placed on a soft and liquid diet for the first few days. The majority of patients feel a tight, stretched sensation, but in a week this feeling subsides.

About six weeks after the surgery, most of the swelling will be reduced, and you’ll be able to see the results of the chin surgery. For the first few weeks, after the surgery strenuous activity should be avoided. After ten days, you’ll be able to resume normal activity. Once you have healed completely you’ll have a face that’s classically shaped and contoured.

When you get ready to go to Thailand for your surgery there are some documents that you must have. Such documents include, medical test (blood pressure, prothronbim, partial thromboplastin times, BUN, CBC, HIV, EKG, and chest x-ray). For chin shaving Thailandyou’ll also need to send a copy of your passport before arriving in Thailand. Make sure that you have all documents in place well before the time of your scheduled surgery date. This will ensure that you’ll have a smooth time of things once you get to Thailand and all you have to worry about is fully recovering.

So once you have everything in order, you can travel to Thailand and get your surgery done that way you can have the chin that you’ve always wanted. There’s no excuse for you to walk around with a chin that you don’t like since you can opt for chin shaving Thailandto get the chin that will make the appearance of your face that much better .

content.title: Forehead Lift in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: For women and men both aging can be a difficult process to go through, therefore, many people go have all sorts of creams and other rituals to make their face look like it did in their younger days. However, sometimes this is not enough so they, instead, decide to have a full facelift.

A full faceliftis suggested for people who are over the age of 40 and are displaying signs of aging. The procedure removes extra skin and then the underlying muscles are tightened. This surgery will help in restoring the skin of the face as well as the neck. When you choose to have this procedure preformed, you’ll also have a mid-facelift, neck lift as well as a forehead lift.

When you come to Thailand for your procedure you should be expect to stay for 10-14 days at least, of course, you can also stay longer and enjoy the beautiful surroundings. Once you arrive in Thailand, you should relax in a hotel after the long flight and then have the surgery the next day. For the facelift you’ll be required to stay four nights in the hospital, and the post operative check-up and stitches will removed after 7-10 days.

The procedure takes 3-4 hours on average and is preformed under general anesthesia. The incision is made above the hairline, in the temple area and is brought in to the front of the ear and then loops behind the ear lobe and along the lower scalp. The face and the neck will be tightened together and the placement of the cuts will be determined by the examination of the structure of the face. During the full faceliftthe patient can also choose to have chin liposuction so the result of the procedure can be enhanced.

content.title: Mini FaceLift - Facelifting in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: The truth of the matter is that all humans have to go through the aging process. As people become older, they age, the effects of sun exposure and gravity, and not to mention the everyday stresses of life are often seen on the face. Such effects can include deep creases between the mouth and the nose, extra fat on the neck and/or slack skin, jowl-like jaw line. The solution to these issues is a mini facelift. The procedure can reverse these effects by removing extra fat and tightening the underlying and re-draping the skin.

Rhytidectomy, another name for this surgery is an operation that restores, of course, the effects of aging on the face, as mentioned above. Over time the stresses of life and other uncontrollable happenings can take a toll on beauty of the face. The once youthful tone of the tissues is lost and begins to sag. The environment and the sun cause lines to set into the surface of your face, which results in wrinkles and lines.

In some cultures the wrinkles and the lines are a display respect and yeas of wisdom, however, in many other cultures this is not the case. The wrinkles and the lines, which make them appear old is, instead, a sign of youth that is loss and competitive edge. So they often to chose to do have the mini facelift procedure preformed. So when you go in for this surgery, how should prepare?

Two weeks before the surgery you should avoid medication that contains aspirin as well as vitamin E. If you’re a smoker then you should either stop smoking or at least cut back to a few every day to decrease the chance of post operative tissues. Two days before the procedure do not drink alcohol. Your surgeon will inform you of anything else about how you should prepare for your mini facelift.

The mini facelift is often completed in combination with eyelid surgery, a forehead lift, chin lift or liposuction so there is an overall renewal of the face. Normally, this procedure can be preformed in outpatient surgical centers or even at physician’s office, which is accredited. The surgeon will begin with making incisions in front of the ear, inside the hairline at the temple.

At this time extra skin is removed and the tightening of the sagging muscles and connective tissues are done. There are some cases, in which, fatty deposits are also removed from under the chin and the neck. Afterwards, the incisions are closed with small sutures. Depending on what other procedures you’re having done the surgery can take between 1-3 hours.

After, the mini facelift there’s a thin, small tube that is temporarily inserted under the skin behind the ear, in order, to drain the blood that can possibly collect there. In addition, the surgeon might as well wrap your head in loose bandages so bruising and swelling is minimized. Recovery takes one week. The sutures, in 10-14 days, are removed.

content.title: Nose Implant Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: The nose is among one of the important features that are on faces. So the shape and the size of the nose is very vital to your overall appearance and the confidence and self-esteem that you have for yourself. If you have a nose that you would like to make some alterations to then you should consider nose implant Thailand.

If you have the desire to change the appearance of your nose by either increasing the bridge of the nose or shaping in such a way that you have a nose that’s more defined then there are nose implant Thailand surgeries that can be preformed to make your wish come true. So start making plans to come to Thailand and get the nose that you always wanted. In addition, you can also have a little vacation.

When you schedule your procedure and travel to Thailand it’s suggested that you plan to stay 14 days at least so the entire process can be complete. One day that you arrive to Thailand, it would be ideal to have a relaxing night in a comfortable hotel after the long flight so that way you can be prepared for the surgery the next day.

The reshaping of the nose requires that you stay one night in the hospital, however, the implant is preformed as an outpatient basis. There are also a post operative check up as well as the removal of stitches that will occur on day seven after the surgery. So what’s the surgery all about?

When you get a nose implant Thailand, the surgeon will place the silicone on the nose’s bridge by making an incision that’s about one centimeters at the sides of the nostrils. Then there’s a pocket that’s made along the ridge of the nose cartilage where the silicone is inserted into.

For the reshaping of the nose, the cuts are placed inside the nose so they’re hidden. Through the incisions, soft tissues that cover the nose are lifted gently which allows for the structure of nose to be reshaped. For the reshaping of the nose, you’ll be put under general anesthesia. On the other hand, for the nose implant the surgery is preformed with local anesthesia.

Once you have the surgery, there will be cold compresses applied on the nose for 2-3 days and you’ll not be allowed to sleep on flat on the face. The bleeding that you’ll experienced will stop after the first day of the surgery. 14 days after nose implant Thailand you should avoid doing any strenuous activities so there won’t be any increased swelling. After 3 months the swelling will settle and the will be completely healed. If you’re worried about the scars keep in mind that the scars will be inside the nose.

As with any surgery that you have preformed, nose implant Thailand include risk, such as bruising, swelling, bleeding, scaring, infection and numbness. However, these risk can be greatly reduced if you make sure to follow the surgeon’s directions.

content.title: Nose Surgery Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: The nose is an important part of the face. It can either make or break the beauty of a face. If the nose isn’t in proportion with the other features of the face sometimes it can throw off the face’s whole look. Nose surgery Thailand, rhinoplasty, which comes from the Greek word Rhinos- “nose” and Plastikos- “to shape” is a procedure that’s performed either by an oral and maxillofacial surgeon, ENT surgeon or a plastic surgeon to improve the look and/or the function of the nose.

A rhinoplasty is normally, preformed to create a better visual or for the purpose of reconstructing to correct defects from birth or problems with breathing. Nose surgery Thailand can be preformed, in addition, to other surgeries such as chin lifts that will result in a better appearance. Depending on what your requirements are you can either increase or decrease the size of your nose.

You can also narrow the nostril spans, alter the angle between the upper lip and the nose, and/or alter the bridge or the tip of the nose, and as motioned above may be able to correct breathing problems. If the rhinoplasty is simple, then normally the surgery can be preformed as an outpatient surgery or the surgery can take place in the surgeon’s office.

Nose surgery Thailand, the majority of the times only take about an hour or two, and you’ll be able to go home almost immediately. If you’re nose job is more complicated then the procedure may have to be done in the hospital and require you have a short stay. The procedure is preformed by a surgeon that has advanced training in both plastic and reconstructive surgery.

Involved with the rhinoplasty, is the re-sculpting of cartilage and the bone. The nose, when it’s operated on by surgeons can choose to either work from inside the nose by making an incision inside the nose, or work from the outside, which requires making a small incision across the tissue that divides the nostrils. This procedure is known as an “open” process.

There are some cases in which nose surgery Thailand, where the surgeon might shape a small piece of a person’s cartilage or bone to increase or strengthen the nose’s structure. This can sometimes be done fore cosmetic reasons , such as to improve shape of the nasal tip or on the other hand, it can be preformed to improve the function of the nose and breathing. You can recovery from the surgery in a few days, and you can return to work/school normally within a week. Your surgeon will inform you about when you can return to your normal activities.

Just as with any surgery you’ll have there are short term side effects, such as in the first few days a small amount of bleeding, puffy face, nose ache, headache, swelling surrounding the eyes and small burst blood vessels that appear as tiny red spots on skin’s surface. There will also be a splint placed on the nose as to make sure that the new shape is maintained. When you finished with nose surgery Thailand you’ll be pleased with the results.

content.title: Upper Eyelid Surgery Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: If you want to improve and enhance yourself so you can have a even more younger looking appearance, in addition, to the lower eyelid surgery, you should also consider having upper eyelid surgery while you’re in Thailand.

During this procedure there’s an incision made along the natural fold of the skin. The upper eyelid surgery removes extra skin and fatty tissue, and then the muscles and the orbital septum can be tightened. The incisions are then closed up carefully. The majority of the surgery is preformed with a very fine eletrocatuery, which controls bleeding if it occurs. Afterwards, very fine stitches are used to close the skin.

When you get to Thailand and have a consultation with your surgeon it’s important that you inform them of any allergies that you may have, serious medical issues you’re dealing with, and medications you’re taking, whether they’re non-prescription or prescription drugs. You should also avoid taking aspirin and any other drugs that might contain aspirin two weeks before you have the surgery.

You and your surgeon will discuss this, but you can either decide to have the upper eyelid surgeryas an outpatient procedure or conducted in the hospital preformed under local or general anesthesia. The surgery can take one hour. Once the surgery is done, your eyes will be lubricated with an ointment and a bandaged may be applied by your surgeon.

There’s a chance that your eyelids may have a tight feeling as the anesthesia begins to wear off, however, any discomfort that you might be feeling will be controlled with pain medication. Of course, you should call your surgeon if the pain is severe.

For several days, your surgeon will require that you keep your head elevated as well as use cold compresses to decrease bruising and swelling. The bruising that you’ll experience will vary since every person is different. During the first week, the bruising will reach it’s peak and will, normally last for two weeks to a month.

You’ll also be shown how to clean your eyes, which you may find gummy for at least a week. Since your eyelids may feel dry, burn and itch there are some doctors that’ll suggest using eye drops. For the first, few weeks after the upper eyelid surgerythere’s a chance that you experience extreme lachrmosity (crying), light sensitivity, and temporary eyesight changes, such as double vision.

To make sure everything is progressing smoothly, for the first two weeks or so the surgeon will closely follow your progress. Two days to a week after the surgery the stitches will be removed, and once they are the swelling and discoloration surrounding the eyes will steadily decrease. The you’ll begin to feel like yourself, but only feel and look even better. You’ll notice that the upper eyelid surgery will cause a dramatic change in your face’s appearance, alleviating the look of old age and tiredness. You’ll be glad to see that your eyes will appear more youthful and fresher.

content.title: Lower Eyelid Surgery in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: The eyes speak volumes to those that come into contact with us. They often can tell others how a person feels, and when they have bags under the eyes it can often say that they’re overworking, tired or the aging process is starting to take hold. For this reason, many decide that they want to change what their eyes says about them and opt to have lower eyelid surgery.

The traditional lower eyelid surgery is preformed by an incision being made just underneath the line of the lash. Extra fat, skin and muscle are removed and surgeons use fine sutures to close up the incision. The permanent stitches are removed after 3-5 days.

If there’s a pocket of fat underneath the lower eyelids, but don’t require the need to have loose skin removed, it may be suggested that you have a transconjunctival blepharoplasty. During this procedure there’s are incision made on the inside of the lower eyelid, which will not leave a visible scar. This surgery is, normally, preformed on younger patients that have fatty lower eyelids. This procedure doesn’t tighten the skin, but instead, decreases the puffiness that’s in the lower lid area.

Before you have the lower eyelid surgery it’s important that you inform the surgeon about any allergies that you have, in addition, to any medical conditions that are serious, and the medications that you are on including non-prescription medications you may be using.

When you get to Thailand, depending on your surgeons as well as your preferences, but the surgery can either be preformed on an outpatient basis or in the hospital or in an ambulatory suite. The surgeon can choose to use local or general anesthesia for performing the surgery. After, the first evening of the surgery you’ll be required to rest quietly and with your head elevated.

A huge help will be to place cold compresses to the eyelids. Your blood pressure will be monitored as to avoid bleeding complications that may affect your vision. Though, you can be up and moving around almost right away, you should have limited activities.

After, you have the lower eyelid surgery you’ll notice that you’ll have larger and more brighter eyes as well as more rested since the loose skin, stretched muscle and extra fat have been removed. Since the skin of the upper eyelid have been removed, which hang down and cause issues with peripheral vision, some people experience improved vision. Of course, the eyes will look more youthful, which is the whole goal of the surgery.

The lower eyelid surgery most likely will smooth out the bulges and remove the bags from underneath the eyes, and cause the skin to be snugger. After the surgery, you’ll no longer look tired and in need in rest and when others look at you they will not be focusing on your lower lids, but think about how great and well-rested you look. The results of this surgery are last longing. So if you’re between the ages of 38 and 50 and want to get rid of your bags then this surgery is ideal for you.

content.title: Breast Implants Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: For any woman breasts are an important feature so since this is the case, the majority of women that don’t have breast large enough to their satisfaction so they’ll take the necessary steps to change their situation. They may do different things to make their breast look larger, but ultimately they come to the conclusion that it’s not just enough so many start to look into enlarging their breast and decide to go for breast implants Thailand.

Thailand is the prefect place to go if you desire to have larger breast. The surgeons in Thailand will ensure that you’ll get the best results possible, however, it’s important that you be realistic in your expectations when considering breast implants Thailand. As long as you have expectations that are realistic then you’ll most likely be happy with the results. So before you have consultation, what should you know?

The first, thing that you have to keep in mind is that this procedure is preformed once the breast have reached their final size, which is after puberty (17-18 years of age). The only exception to this is in cases of breast asymmetry or congenital breast hyperplasia then the procedure can be preformed earlier.

When you decide on breast implants Thailandyou have to consider three possible areas in which the implant can be placed. The first, possibility and most common is to insert it in the lower fold of the breast. This enables the surgeon full excess and the scar is hidden in this area. The second, possibility is through the areola. Making an incision in this area provides the best results and it as well is the only method that goes through the breast tissue. This means that there may be a risk of infection, in addition, to loss of sensation is higher.

The last, possible area for the incision is through the armpits. There are some plastic surgeons that prefer this method because the scar that’s created is virtually invisible, unless, of course, if you wear sleeveless tops. The one disadvantage that may come with this incision is slight asymmetry of the breast. However, you and the surgeon will make the final decision as to what incision method is right for you.Another, important thing that you have to make a decision about is what shape of implants you’d like to have. There are two different shapes that you can choose from. The first, is a round shape and the other is pear shaped, which is also called “anatomic implants” since the shape is similar to the contour of a natural breast. However, these are more expensive and a larger incision is required during the surgery. So this is a matter that you have to think carefully about when going through breast implants Thailand.

After, the surgery you’ll be required to wear a bandage or a sports bra at all times for a month. Once three months have passed after the surgery, optimal results can normally be seen after you finish with your breast implants Thailand.

content.title: Breast Lift Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Sometimes without even realizing it the aging process starts to take hold and parts of the body that use to sit up high or sitting low and some areas of the body are widening out and dropping. There’s not a whole lot that can be done without the intervention of surgery so many women decide that once their breast begin to sag whether it’s due to aging or other life happening the solution for this problem is breast lift Thailand.

There are various ways that breast lift Thailandcan be preformed. However, the most common technique involves an anchor-shaped incision, which follows the natural contour of the breast. Where the cut is made, the incision outlines the sections which the skin from the breast is removed and then creates a new locale for the nipple.

When the extra skin is removes, then the nipple and the areola are moved to a higher position. The skin that surrounds the areola is brought down together, in order, to reshape the breast. Normally, there are stitches that are placed around the areola in a straight vertical line that extends from the area of the nipple and along the lower fold of the breast.

There are some patients who opt for breast lift Thailand, especially for the women that have breast that are small and have sagging that is minimal, might be a candidate for a modifies procedure that has the requirement of less incisions. For instance, the procedure is done in a “doughnut or concentric mastopexy”, which are circular incisions that are made around the area of the areola. There’s also a doughnut shaped area of shin that’s removed.

If there’s a patient that’s having implants as well during the breast lift, then the surgeon will place it in the pocket that is directly underneath the breast tissue, or either deeper under the chest wall muscle. During the surgery, the surgeon will make the effort to ensure that the scars left from the breast as unnoticeable as possible. Although, the surgeon will do his best it’s best to remember that mastopexy scars are permanent and extensive.

Your breast may remain red and lumpy for a few months, and over time it’ll become less noticeable, and may even fade into white thin lines. Happily, the surgeon can make the incisions in an area in which it cannot be seen and you’ll even be able to wear tops that are low cut after breast lift Thailand.It’s important to keep close in mind that while the risk are low for complications are low you still need to be aware of them.

The possible risk for breast lift Thailandare separated into two groups. The first group, which are the main risk, include bruising, swelling, infection, scar, numbness and bleeding. In the second group, which are specific for the breast lift procedure, is damage to the supply of blood to the nipple and a thick scar. In addition, breast feeding may not be a possibility. Another, important thing to note is that breast lift doesn’t increase the risk of breast reduction, but the risk may even slightly decline.

content.title: Breast Reduction Thailand- Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Women that have small breast often envy other women that have larger breast, however, what they don’t know is that women that have large breast suffer. Women that have breast that are too big often times suffer from issues like skin infections under the folds of the breast, have a difficult time breathing and suffer from back pain. None of these conditions are no picnic so many opt for surgery and consider breast reduction Thailand.

When the surgery is being preformed, skin and breast tissue and extra fat are eliminated and then the surgeon created smaller breast that’s just right for the woman’s body proportions. There are two ways in which breast reduction Thailandcan be done. One process involves a long scar or what is called and “anchor” scar is the method of choice for women with breast that are very large.

There is a cut made through the nipple, by the surgeon, and then behind the folds of the breast. Then the nipple is lifted and the breast are shaped. The second, process involves a smaller cut, which is for breast that are medium sized. The incision is made through the nipple only and through the fold as well. There are times when extra skin isn’t removed fully, which results in some folds of skin underneath the breast. However, not to worry, they normally, disappear within 3-5 months.

Of course, you have to keep in mind that every surgery comes with risk. The risk that are associated with breast implants include, difficulties in scar healing and wound infections. There may be a chance that there will be asymmetry where the nipple is positioned and might not be able to breast feed. All of these risk are important to consider when deciding on breast reduction Thailand.

After, the breast reduction there are some surgeons that prefer to apply an bra or and elastic bandage. Then there are some surgeons that will use drainage tubes to allow secretions and extra blood to drain. There’s a chance that you’ll experience pain when you make sharp movements or cough, and you’ll have the aid of pain killers to reduce the discomfort.

Within a few days, after the surgery you’ll be able to return to your every day activities, however, you should keep from doing anything strenuous for a month. After, breast reduction Thailandit’s suggested that you refrain from smoking since it can interfere with your healing process of the scars. It’s also recommended that for 1-2 weeks that you avoid sexual activity.

The scars and the bruises that result from the surgery, normally go away after a few weeks and six month after the surgery the final results can be noticed. The appearance of your breast, afterward, will be impacted by weight changes and any pregnancies. It’s also important to note that. Although, after breast reduction Thailandyour breast will be smaller, if you had back pain before it’s possible that you can still have pain, however, the pain will not worsen.

content.title: Buttock Lift Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: There’s no need for you to feel bad about your sagging buttocks when there’s an affordable buttocks lift in Thailand  that will solve the problem for you . With this procedure you can have the butt that you had in your younger days and get back the confidence that you had as well. So if you want to improve the saggy buttocks seriously consider a butt lift.

Buttocks lift Thailand, should not be mixed up with buttock implants or body contouring. This procedures has the goal to improve the tone and tautness of the skin on your buttocks. This surgery is meant to address the issue of skin that’s sagging in the buttock area that is a result of weight loss, genetics, gravity or age. The butt lift will tighten the skin that’s drooping and reposition the buttock in such a manner that the tone and contour is improved. Basically, what this procedure does is provides a more normal shape and contour to your bottom.

When performing the procedure, first the surgeon makes an incision from hipbone to hipbone on your back. From the structures that are underlying the skin and the fat is separated. The excess skin as well as the fat are removed. There’s a temporary tube that’s inserted to allow drainage of excess fluid from the surgical area before the incision is stitched up. When the incision is closed, gauze and elastic compression are applied to the area.

The procedure can take anywhere from three to six areas, but it depends on the extent of the treatment you’re having done. Once the lift is completed you’ll be required to stay in the hospital for two nights. You must be aware that this surgery, as with any other, have risk involved. During the post-operative buttocks lift Thailandyou should not sit on the buttocks since they’re healing from the surgery. While, you’re recovering, you may suffer from a fair amount of pain when there’s any stress applied to the area.

The chances are rare, but complications can include, hematoma, numbness of the skin, bruising, drainage of fluid, scarring and discomfort. Pulmonary embolism can also occur, but is rear. If you want to have this surgery done you have to be a candidate. You’re a candidate if you have skin of the hip that has lost its elasticity or if you have saggy skin in the thigh or buttock area.

When you undergo buttocks lift Thailandyou’ll be able to see that your thigh and buttock skin are tighter and more attractive, and have an improved contour and decreases irregularities on the surface of the skin. So you know that when you come to Thailand for this surgery that you’ll go home with a buttocks that you won’t be able to help but show off.
The great thing about buttocks lift Thailand, not only will you be able to improve the way your buttocks looks, but you’re also get the chance to relax in a beautiful country.

The chances are rare, but complications can include, hematoma, numbness of the skin, bruising, drainage of fluid, scarring and discomfort. Pulmonary embolism can also occur, but is rear. If you want to have this surgery done you have to be a candidate. You’re a candidate if you have skin of the hip that has lost its elasticity or if you have saggy skin in the thigh or buttock area. When you undergo buttocks lift Thailandyou’ll be able to see that your thigh and buttock skin are tighter and more attractive, and have an improved contour and decreases irregularities on the surface of the skin. So you know that when you come to Thailand for this surgery that you’ll go home with a buttocks that you won’t be able to help but show off. The great thing about buttocks lift Thailand, not only will you be able to improve the way your buttocks looks, but you’re also get the chance to relax in a beautiful country. content.title: Buttocks Implant in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: For some, they may think that their butts are way to big and wish they can rid of it. On the other hand there are others that what nothing more than to have a bigger and fuller butt, and try everything to gain the appearance of a plumper bottom and seek out buttock implants Thailand. When they undergo this surgery, they can finally have the apple bottom they’ve been desiring.

This surgical procedure, which is also known as gluteoplasty, is designed to reshape the size of your bottom and also create a more firm, and enhanced appearance. Since this area of the body isn’t easily altered by the loss of weight or regular exercise, so this option is worth considering to improve the way your buttocks look. Generally, anyone that wishes to undergo buttock implants Thailand that’s in good physically health can have this procedure done.

This procedure is preformed by using fat. It’s ideal to remove fat from other parts of the body and then injected into the buttocks. The benefit of using this method is that there is a less likely chance that there’ll be a rejection since the tissue that is used is taken from your body. In addition, using this technique can also result in a more natural appearance. The fat that’s used normally comes from the body where there’s extra fat, such as the flank area, upper and lower buttock.

The excess fat, that is moved from these areas can as well reshape your buttock so it likes as if you have had a butt lift. Once the fat has been removed there’s a special process that it goes through and is then injected into your buttocks with a cannula (small tube), which will make for minimal scars. During the buttock implants Thailand, the biggest challenged of the fat grafting is to make sure that the graft is able to survive in the new location.

This can be accomplished by injecting small amounts of fat into the layers each at a time, above and below the butt muscles. Performing this surgery in this matter will result in better blood supply is accomplished and the irregularities of the surface are reduced. Still, the survival of the graft is still not sure. Generally, it’s thought that whatever fat still remains will be permanent.

Normally, after buttock implants Thailand there is no discomfort, however, the pain comes from the incisions that were made in the donor area. Keep in mind that there are risk with any procedure that you undergo, however, the risk for this procedure is minimal. The main risk that you should be aware of is the fat absorption that occurs in about one-third of patients. Infection, scaring and bleeding are rare.

3-5 days after buttock implants Thailand you’ll be able to return to work, but there are special garments that you’ll be required to wear for 3-4 weeks. It might be up to one month before you start to feel normal again. There’ll also be swelling, but that’ll subside in a couple of months.

content.title: Liposuction in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: A perfectly sculpted body that is able to carry of any fashionable outfit, particularly a little string bikini for a day at the beach is something sought after the world over. Exercise and diet play a major role, but for some cellulite and a genetic predisposition to fatty deposits in areas like the thighs, arms, stomach and buttocks is unavoidable. Liposuction in Thailand is an ideal answer to those who wish to sculpt their bodies to be bikini beautiful.

Liposuction is a procedure that removes excess fatty tissue and cellulite from problematic areas in the body and the treatment can be administered to correct problem areas where excess fat is stored in the body. It can smooth the lumpy appearance of thighs, can sculpt the stomach and buttocks, the waist and arms and can even be used to minimise a double chin.

The ideal candidate for liposuction is anyone who has excessive fatty deposits that they would like to have removed from problematic areas in the body. Liposuction not only removes the fat but reshapes the contours of the body.

A small incision is made and a cannula is inserted. The cannula is a long thin hollow tube that is connected to a powerful suction pump. The cannula is inserted between the skin and the muscle, in the pockets of fatty tissue. The excess fatty tissue is removed using this powerful suction device and creates hollow tunnels in the fat that collapse after the procedure, rendering a slimmer, more contoured appearance.
The patient can expect a slimmer, more toned appearance leading to a boost in self-confidence and an improved self-image.

Excessive liposuction, where too much fatty tissue is removed at once can result in toxicity and in the patients skin having an uneven and even lumpy appearance. This can be associated with nausea, vomiting, excessive pain, bruising, swelling, slow wound healing, skin irregularities and depressions, blood clots and injury to abdominal organs.
The patient can be discharged between 1 – 3 hours after the procedure and there is usually no need for them remain in hospital overnight.
Scarring is not usually an issue as very small incisions are made to insert the cannula.
Local or general anaesthesia is administered before the surgery.

Most patients are able to return to a normal desk-type job after two days, but the time varies from patient to patient and some may experience soreness for a longer time, though generally recovery is swift.
The effects of liposuction should be long lasting provided the patient does not gain a significant amount of weight, which will result in the re-growth of

content.title: Lipoplasty in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: It can be very, very frustrating when you work and work out and still cannot get rid of excess fat in particular areas in the body. It makes exercising and having a well-balanced diet pointless. However, there’s something that you can do that’ll solve your problem of unwanted fat, lipoplasty Thailand.

If you’re a person that suffers from having pockets of extra fat in certain spots of the body that cannot be removed by conducting exercise on a regular basis as well as control of diet is the ideal candidate for this surgery. In addition, to having extra fat, the condition of your health is also important. This means that you have to be healthy physically, realistic in your expectations and psychologically stable if you want to have lipoplasty Thailand. If you suffer from such medical issues, such as heart or lung disease, diabetes or have had surgery close to the area in which needs lipo then you’ll have higher risk of complications.

When you have this procedure done, you’ll be required to stay in Thailand for about 10-14 days, in order, to complete the entire process and have a full recovery after the surgery. You’ll spend one night in the hotel before your surgery. This will aid in keeping your blood pressure down and give your body the opportunity to adjust to the new environment. Seven days after the surgery there will be a follow up, which you stitches will be removed. Within these two weeks you’ll also have ample time to recovery before heading back home.

Of course, after you have lipoplasty Thailandyou can always stay in Thailand for a couple more days that way you can combine your surgery with a little vacation as you recover from your procedure. So when you plan out your surgery as a vacation you’ll be able to take your time to relax and fully recover from your procedure and enjoy some of the local culture and return home refreshed.

Before, you have the surgery there are some things that you must do, in order, to prepare yourself for the surgery. Two weeks before the date of the procedure you have to stop using tobacco products, drinking alcohol, stop any medication as well as vitamins. You must also fast, in addition, for eight hours before the surgery so this means you’ll not be able to eat anything on the day of the surgery.

You must also understand the procedure involved with lipoplasty Thailand, and the risk before you have the surgery. So it’s important to make sure that you do your homework and ask your surgeon any questions you have before the surgery.

After lipoplasty Thailand, there are some guidelines for post-operative care. You’ll have to make sure to wrap the area with a compression sheet for few weeks as to firm the muscles and to decrease swelling. The swelling that you’re experience will subside within one month and will settle within three to six months. As long as you’re committed to a healthy life-style the changes are permanent.

content.title: Tummy Tuck Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: The way that you feel about yourself is very important as well as the way others view you. So for this reason, the majority of people take great pains to make sure that they look their best, in order, to keep up their appearance. However, there are times that that having a balanced diet and exercising doesn’t cut it, especially if you’re trying to eliminate the tummy and create a flat stomach, therefore, they may opt to have tummy tuck Thailand.

A tummy tuck, also known as an abdominoplasty, is a surgery that flattens the stomach by the removal of extra fat and skin surrounding the stomach as well as tightening the abdominal muscles. If you suffer from loose skin caused by extreme weight loss or muscles that have become weak because of pregnancy then having a tummy tuck will be able to improve this problem area. This procedure can dramatically improve the look of your abdomen.

So you’re a good candidate for tummy tuck Thailandif you have large fat deposits or lose and sagging skin surrounding the stomach area. Not only that, it’s vital that you have a realistic and clear expectation of what you wish to accomplish. You should keep in mind, however, that if you’re planning to lose weight or get pregnant then you should wait to undergo the surgery. It’s also noteworthy, that the fat deposits are limited to the area underneath the belly button so you may also want to consider a mini tummy tuck as well.

You should keep in mind that no matter how cautious your surgeon is while performing the surgery, there are always risk, however, the rate of complications occurring are minimal. The surgeons that conduct theses surgeries are experienced and highly trained. So you can consider it a safe move to have a tummy tuck in Thailand. In addition, to being safe going to Thailand for a tummy tuck you can also save up to 70% when compared to having the surgery done in North America, Europe and Australia.

When you have tummy tuck Thailandyou should expect to stay for 8-10 days. You’ll be required to have a 3 night stay in the hospital, and seven days after the surgery you’ll have a follow up. So this leaves you time to have sort of a mini vacation since you have the choice to recover at a beach resort. This recovery time in a beautiful place will optimize your healing and you’ll be back to yourself in no time fully relaxed.

If you have realistic expectations of tummy tuck Thailandand want to have a flatter stomach that you can be proud of then you should consider having this procedure done. You can come to Thailand for the procedure where you’ll have the best surgery and care by experienced surgeons, in addition, you can relax in a beautiful country and learn about a new culture and go home refreshed and renewed.

If you suffer from loose skin caused by extreme weight loss or muscles that have become weak because of pregnancy then having a tummy tuck will be able to improve this problem area. This procedure can dramatically improve the look of your abdomen. So you’re a good candidate for tummy tuck Thailandif you have large fat deposits or lose and sagging skin surrounding the stomach area. Not only that, it’s vital that you have a realistic and clear expectation of what you wish to accomplish. You should keep in mind, however, that if you’re planning to lose weight or get pregnant then you should wait to undergo the surgery. It’s also noteworthy, that the fat deposits are limited to the area underneath the belly button so you may also want to consider a mini tummy tuck as well. You should keep in mind that no matter how cautious your surgeon is while performing the surgery, there are always risk, however, the rate of complications occurring are minimal. The surgeons that conduct theses surgeries are experienced and highly trained. So you can consider it a safe move to have a tummy tuck in Thailand. In addition, to being safe going to Thailand for a tummy tuck you can also save up to 70% when compared to having the surgery done in North America, Europe and Australia. When you have tummy tuck Thailandyou should expect to stay for 8-10 days. You’ll be required to have a 3 night stay in the hospital, and seven days after the surgery you’ll have a follow up. So this leaves you time to have sort of a mini vacation since you have the choice to recover at a beach resort. This recovery time in a beautiful place will optimize your healing and you’ll be back to yourself in no time fully relaxed. If you have realistic expectations of tummy tuck Thailandand want to have a flatter stomach that you can be proud of then you should consider having this procedure done. You can come to Thailand for the procedure where you’ll have the best surgery and care by experienced surgeons, in addition, you can relax in a beautiful country and learn about a new culture and go home refreshed and renewed. content.title: Vaser in Thailand - Vaser Liposelection
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Vaser liposuction Thailand or LipoSelection Thailand as it is also known, is a form of cosmetic surgery that is designed to remove build ups of excess fact from the skin leaving firmer, younger body shape. It is designed to target specific areas that are mostly unaffected by diet and exercise. It is just one of several innovative approaches to removing the fat with great results..

Vaser Lipo uses ultrasonic energy to selectively break down fat deposits for easy and safe removal. As it is a minimally invasive procedure with success rates, the procedure has become very popular for men and women. Vaser Liposuction can be used to remove fat from nearly all parts of the body except the face and other sensitive areas. Vaser Lipo surgery is perfect for everything from minor adjustments to major changes. Moreover, VASER can be used for areas of the body re-sculpting to make them appear more toned and muscular

While technology and equipment have been constantly improved, ultrasonic energy is used to break up fat deposits has been used for a number of years. The beauty of this is that you can be safe in the knowledge that the surgeons were exposed to the different techniques proposed. The energy that is used in Vaser Liposuction is tissue selective, which means that the ultrasound energy targets unwanted fat, but preserves other surrounding tissues such as nerves, blood vessels and connective tissue, promote smooth contours and reduce healing time. Therefore, liposuction surgery vaser provides a faster and improved surgery healing time.

The surgeon begins the operation by making a small incision in the selected area. The fat layer is then infused with tumescent fluid. A small probe, which transmits ultrasonic energy is then inserted. The probe is used to selectively break the stubborn fat cells and emulsify into the liquid infusion. The emulsified fat is then removed using a specially designed suction cannula VentX.

As the procedure only requires a small incision and no physical force whatsoever, the payback period is much shorter than traditional liposuction. Moreover, no suturing or sewing is necessary, therefore, during the healing process, the skin retracts seamlessly to give firmer looking, smoother and more natural feel. However, some scars are inevitable. Patients can expect to resume their normal activities within 1-2 weeks, depending on the area treated and amount of fat removed.

In addition to a reduced recovery period, Vaser liposuction also has a number of other advantages over other forms of fat removal. Vaser Lipo surgery is performed under local anesthesia, so there is usually no need for an overnight stay, the risks are as small as it is not an invasive surgery, more fat can be removed at a time and the overall benefits are remarkable.

content.title: Male to Female Thailand - MTF Thailand
h1: Male to Female Thailand – MTF Thailand
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: Once you have made that decision to go from male to female, and have gone through all the required steps the next step that you have to take is sex reassignment. When you’re ready to take this you should consider male to female Thailand. You’ll be able to get away and concentrate on what your goal is and recovery in peace in a beautiful country and return home as a new person. However, before you start making the plans to travel to Thailand there are some things that you should be aware of.

If you want to undergo male to female Thailand then you have to meet the requirement of being 18 years of age or older. If you’re under the age of 20, you have to have the permission from your parents.   In addition, you have to be diagnosed with either gender dysphoria, gender identity disorder or another disorder, such as anxiety or depression.  You must have also undergone one year at least or antiandrogens  and/or hormones. I

It’s required that you have lived in the cross-gender role for at least one year full-time.  Lastly, you must have the approval from a clinical psychologist, psychiatric social worker or from a psychiatrist.  Once you have met of the requirements you’re ready for the surgery. The surgery involves a combination of  penile skin inversion as well as an immediate full thickness skin graft. The vaginal canal and the opening is created underneath the urethral opening and prostate gland.

Since vaginal depth is the biggest concern for most people, you should keep in mind that the factor in creating the depth is the amount of penile shaft skin.  The method for male to female Thailand that lengthens the vaginas depth is using the full thickness of the skin graft from the scrotal.  The hair that’s on the scrotum is removed so the skin graft is placed at the distal end of the penile skin flap.

By using this method it can lengthen the depth 2 more inches at least.  The operation will last about 3 hours. Before being released from the hospital to the hotel, there’ll be a nurse to explain how to care for the vagina as well as prescribe more medication. In 7-10 days the stitches will be removed, and you can return home.   The neovagina will be functional within 6 weeks after.

As mentioned, 6 weeks after the male to female Thailand you’re able to engage in neovaginal intercourse. There is some virginal lubrication during sexual arousal, however, you should apply lubricant jelly at the opening of the vagina before intercourse. It’s typical, during arousal that there’ll be mild swelling of the urethral meatus which can be corrected with cosmetic improvement.

So when you have male to female Thailand you’ll afterwards be able to function as a women. Since you’re Thailand you’ll be able to fully recover and have some new experiences as well as learn about a new culture.  When you’re entirely recovered from the surgery you’ll be able to go back home and start a new life.

content.title: Female to Male Thailand - FTM Thailand
h1: Female to Male Thailand – FTM Thailand
h2: ( click to enlarge )
WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: The decision to make the transformation from a female to a male is not an easy choice to make. There are a lot of steps and processes that one has to go through, however, on the decision has been made and you have gone through the required steps you can finally go on your to leading the life you were meant to live, and to make your transformation full circle, you should consider female to male Thailand.

In order, to be approved for this procedure there are certain requirements that you must meet. These requirements include, being 18 or over, but if you’re under the age of 20 you’ll need parent’s permission. If you’re considering this operation you have to be diagnosed with gender dysphoria and gender identity disorder or another associated condition.  To undergo female to male Thailand you must have undergone a year of antiandrgens and/or female hormones, and have to have lived in the cross-gender role full-time for a year.  Lastly, you must attain the approval from a psychiatric social worker, clinical psychologist or a psychiatrist is required.

This procedure has 3steps in order to complete the female to male transformation. The first, stage is conducting a subcutaneous mastectomy, hysterectomy, in addition, to an oophoretomy. Basically, the breast are removed as well as the womb and the ovaries.  Stage two, involves penile reconstruction by using a sensate radial forearm free flap including a malleable silicone rod. Stage 3, is the creation of testicle implant, which can either be done with or without tissue expansion.

After the surgery is completed,  you should be aware of the fact that there’ll be no sensation in the penis, the urine flow might leak, which will require many correction surgeries and most importantly the appearance of the penis will not 100% look like a male. All these things you should consider before undergoing female to male Thailand.  Before you are released from the hospital to go to your hotel the nurse you show how to take care of yourself and prescribe some medication.  In 7-10 days the stitches are removed and you’re all set to go home.

So when you travel to Thailand you should prepare yourself to stay at least one month to complete the surgery and recover. The great thing about that is you’ll be able to relax and enjoy your stay in Thailand and have a peaceful recovery before heading home. While, you’re here you’ll discover all the things that are offered.

There are a lot of steps and processes that one has to go through, however, on the decision has been made and you have gone through the required steps you can finally go on your to leading the life you were meant to live, and to make your transformation full circle, you should consider female to male Thailand. In order, to be approved for this procedure there are certain requirements that you must meet. These requirements include, being 18 or over, but if you’re under the age of 20 you’ll need parent’s permission. If you’re considering this operation you have to be diagnosed with gender dysphoria and gender identity disorder or another associated condition.  To undergo female to male Thailand you must have undergone a year of antiandrgens and/or female hormones, and have to have lived in the cross-gender role full-time for a year.  Lastly, you must attain the approval from a psychiatric social worker, clinical psychologist or a psychiatrist is required. This procedure has 3steps in order to complete the female to male transformation. The first, stage is conducting a subcutaneous mastectomy, hysterectomy, in addition, to an oophoretomy. Basically, the breast are removed as well as the womb and the ovaries.  Stage two, involves penile reconstruction by using a sensate radial forearm free flap including a malleable silicone rod. Stage 3, is the creation of testicle implant, which can either be done with or without tissue expansion. After the surgery is completed,  you should be aware of the fact that there’ll be no sensation in the penis, the urine flow might leak, which will require many correction surgeries and most importantly the appearance of the penis will not 100% look like a male. All these things you should consider before undergoing female to male Thailand.  Before you are released from the hospital to go to your hotel the nurse you show how to take care of yourself and prescribe some medication.  In 7-10 days the stitches are removed and you’re all set to go home. So when you travel to Thailand you should prepare yourself to stay at least one month to complete the surgery and recover. The great thing about that is you’ll be able to relax and enjoy your stay in Thailand and have a peaceful recovery before heading home. While, you’re here you’ll discover all the things that are offered. Although, there’s a lot involved with female to male Thailand the result will be worth it.  When you get ready to go home you’ll have the body that you’ve always wanted and be able to live the life that you desire, and Thailand is the prefect place to come and have your surgery. content.title: Hair Transplants in Thailand - Bangkok and Samui
h2: WOULD YOU LIKE TO GET SURGEON FEEDBACK?
paragraphs: As humans there are some things that we have no control over and hair loss is one of those things. The loss of hair can be a result of a combination of genetics, hormonal changes, and of course, aging. For some hair loss my begin earlier due to more severe baldness. Other reasons for hair loss, include burns or trauma. Having hair loss have a great impact on how you feel about yourself when you look in the mirror. No matter what the reason for hair loss hair transplant Thailandcan restore it.

Hair transplant Thailandprocedure involves the resurfacing of bald areas of the scalp with hair. The plugs of a bald scalp are removed and are filled with plugs of scalp that contains numerous hair roots that are taken from the hair-bearing areas. The grafts take root into the locations and the hair follicles and eventually they will start to grow.

The number of the grafts that will be required and the length of treatment for you will be determined on the degree of baldness. In some cases, there may be a need to have several operations. You should be aware that using this technique may leave behind small scars on the donor sites, but they are not normally noticeable. There are also other options for hair transplants.

Scalp flap finder, is another option if the above is not for you. Hair transplant Thailandis preformed by the sides of the scalp, above the ears, and the back of the scalp is bearing hair. A long “flap” of the scalp that has hair is removed and is placed across the bald area to generate growth of hair. Included, in the treatment, portions of the bald scalp might removed.

The site where the hair was taken is closed by stretching the other side of the scalp. The procedure will replace hair across a large span of bald scalp. When the hair begins to grow, it’ll look normal and the scars are hidden in the hair follicles. Another, option is tissue expansion. In this procedure, there’s a tissue expander that’s inserted under the hair growth area situated adjacent to the bald area.

After a few weeks, the expander will cause the skin to produce new skin cells. Then there will be another operation to place the expanded skin over the adjoining area of baldness. You’ll be an ideal candidate for hair transplant Thailandif you have healthy hair growth in the back and the sides of your head. The hair that are found in these locations will act as the donor sites in which the flaps and the grafts will be removed.

When you have hair transplant Thailand, the procedure can take place in either the surgeons office-based surgical facility, hospital outpatient, hospital in patient or in an outpatient surgery center. To perform the surgery, your surgeon may choose to use general or local anesthetic, which is combined with a sedative that allows you to remain relax during the procedure, but awake.

content.title: Medical Questionnaire
h2: Surgeon will carefully review your case and prepare an initial evaluation, including a price quote for procedure(s).
paragraphs: Taking & submitting photographs:To allow a cosmetic surgeon to make the most comprehensive assessment of your case and provide the best possible recommendation for your surgery, please do your best to take your photographs in the following format.
Your photographs are kept instrict confidenceand only shared with doctors who are assigned to handle your medical procedure.

The first and most essential step to a successful surgery is for doctor to learn as much about patient as possible. This Medical Questionnaire helps our plastic surgeons determine if you are medically qualified for your surgery.

After you fill out the Questionnaire, a plastic surgeon from your preferred hospital will carefully review your case and prepare an initial evaluation, including a price quote for procedure(s) of your choice.
Beauty Med representative will share the doctor’s preliminary evaluation and price quote with you, answer any questions you may have, and schedule a surgery date.

Beauty Med will help arrange your trip to Thailand, including taking care of all hospital administrative and patient admission procedures, airport pick up, hospital/hotel transfers, and more — absolutely free for you.
Information you provide in this Questionnaire will become part of your private medical record, used only by the hospital where you have your operation.
All data, including images is sent through an encrypted SSL protocol.

content.title: Preecha's Aesthetic Institute - Cosmetic Surgery Clinic in Thailand
h1: Preecha’s Aesthetic Institute – Cosmetic Surgery Clinic in Thailand
paragraphs: PAI clinic is located in the heart of Bangkok on Thonglor area, and it is considered the biggest clinic in ASIA.It consists of three floors, the first floor where the evaluations are done, the second floor is the dermatology laser center, and the recovery rooms, and finally the last floor is the operations room.At PAI we have around 5 top thai and american board plastic surgeons that are considered the fathers of cosmetic surgeries in Thailand with more than 30 years experience.

Minor surgeries are performed at PAI Clinic and major surgeries that require general anesthesia are done eithor in Chamillian Hospital or Piyavate Hospital under PAI plastic surgeons.What made PAI surgeons so successful is the leadership of Dr. Preecha the top surgeon in Thailand and one of the highly skilled surgeons in the world. The leadership was brilliant by making all plastic surgeons on his team to have a standard technique (his technique).

content.title: Kamol Cosmetic Hospital
paragraphs: The Kamol Cosmetic Hospital in Bangkok, offers one of the best and successful sex change surgery procedures in Thailand. The surgeons of this hospital are offering a wide range of the surgical procedures from the 1st to the last stage of the gender transitions from male to female with wide range medical facilities and complete functionality. They also offer female to male surgeries and other normal procedures for non-srs patietns.

This hospital can offer the best aesthetically prepared to resemble actual female genitalia. The surgeons of this hospital performs uncountable gender reassignment surgery and combined cosmetic procedures per year. So, it is the best hospital to rectify the sex change complication of the patient. It is the suitable way to change sex through this hospital and feel a different life in single segment.   The surgical packages can specify what are the services included and can outline among some other things, number of days that are included for the post treatment care at hospital, equipment that is available, room type, meal as well as medical tests at Kamol Cosmetic Hospital. Any of the additional days that are spent in hospital ad optional extras are charged to patient.

Kamol Cosmetic Hospital will arrange documentation in English required for the followup care in patient’s home country. Hospitals as well have the services to facilitate the claims from an insurance. These are some international hospitals & treatment centres with the dedicated services for the international patients.

Kamol Cosmetic Hospital, not just you will get the highest quality of medical service, however you can as well rest assured you can get most personalized treatment, and follow-up from the doctors on going basis. Thus, you may also have confidence in every step of Center’s medical services. Dr. Kamol makes over 100 sex change operations every year.

content.title: Bangpakok 9 International Hospital
paragraphs: Bangpakok9 International Hospital is a tertiary private care hospital located in Bangkok, Thailand. We are committed to providing healthcare with world-class standards. The Bangpakok Hospital Group has a total of 6 hospitals within the chain, all under the same high standard of management and dedication to customer care.Our specialist centers include; heart center, plastic surgery center, anti-aging center, aesthetic and skin center, orthopedic center, cancer center, rehabilitation center, dental center and and children’s center, to name but a few.

Only a 30-minute drive from Bangkok’s Suvamabhumi Airport, Bangpakok9 International Hospital is located a little south of Central Bangkok, in the area of Bangpakok, near the world-famous Chao Phraya River.Bangpakok9 International Hospital has physicians trained to the highest International standard, operating with the very latest medical equipment. Many of our doctors trained medicine abroad, and have obtained the finest medical education from chulalongkron Medical School, the most prestigious university in Thailand.This allows us to promote an international standard of healthcare at Bangpakok 9 International Hospital and earns us unconditional trust from our patients. .

content.title: Bangkok Hospital Samui
h1: Samui Clinic – Samui Hospital – Bangkok Hospital
paragraphs: Bangkok Hospital Samui belongs is a branch of a network of 18 private hospitals all overThailand. It is situated on the resort island of Koh Samui and offers a full range of medical facilities.

The Bangkok Hospital group is one of the most advanced medical groups in Southeast Asia, featuring state-of-the-art technology and a full roster of well-trained employees. Cosmetic Surgeons and specialists are trained in the latest techniques and have often received their formal education in North America or Europe.

The hospital’s up-to-date facilities include two modern operational theaters, a CT-64 slice, Ultrasound 4, a Hemodialysis unit,D  and a fully-stocked blood bank. It also boasts Emergency and Trauma unit with well-equipped ambulances.

Specialized clinics within the hospital include Neurosurgery, Cardiology, Psychiatry, Nephrology, Ear, Nose and Throat (ENT), Pediatrics, Obstetrics & Gynecology, Oncology, Orthopedics and Beauty Center. The inpatient department is equipped with six fully-equipped ICU beds.

More than half of the patients at Bangkok Hospital Samui are foreigners, and among these only a small percentage are part of local expatriate communities. Most of the patients are enrolled in medical tourism packages. The staff is well-versed in medical tourism and can assist patients with paperwork, travel arrangements and even airport pickups.
